### ALGORITHM ###

Step 1: Start the program.
Step 2: Create a list a with initial elements [10, 20, 30, 40] and print it.
Step 3: Add the element 50 to the end of the list using append().
Step 4: Add multiple elements [60, 70] to the end of the list using extend().
Step 5: Insert the value 15 at index position 1 using insert().
Step 6: Remove the first occurrence of the value 30 from the list using remove().
Step 7: Remove and print the last element of the list using pop().
Step 8: Find and print the index position of the value 40.
Step 9: Count and print how many times the value 20 appears in the list.
Step 10: Sort the list in ascending order using sort().
Step 11: Reverse the order of the list using reverse().
Step 12: Create a copy of the list and store it in a new variable b.
Step 13: Calculate and print the length, maximum value, minimum value, and sum of the elements in the list.
Step 14: Empty the list entirely using clear() and print the empty list.
Step 15: Stop the program.


